title: Falcon Heavy delay affects space station manifest
summary: A delayed launch of commercial satellites on a Falcon Heavy could upend the schedule of flights to the International Space Station, including a private astronaut mission that was scheduled for early May.

title: SpaceX Receives Permission To Lease Historic SLC-6 At Vandenberg Space Force Base
summary: Vandenberg Space Force Base has granted SpaceX permission to lease Space Launch Complex 6 for Falcon rocket launches.

title: NASA InSight Study Provides Clearest Look Ever at Martian Core
summary: A pair of quakes in 2021 sent seismic waves deep into the Red Planet’s core, giving scientists the best data yet on its size and composition.

title: Ursa Major to supply upper-stage engine for Astra’s new rocket
summary: Rocket propulsion startup Ursa Major announced April 24 that Astra Space selected the company’s Hadley liquid engine to power the upper stage of its new Rocket 4 launch vehicle.

title: Report: Space Force could benefit from commercial data to monitor satellites and debris
summary: The Space Force is investing in new sensors and technologies to better characterize objects in orbit, but is not taking full advantage of commercially available data and services, says a new report by the Government Accountability Office.

title: SpaceX aims to launch Falcon Heavy and two Falcon 9 rockets this week
summary: SpaceX will aim to complete three successful launches this week, with Falcon Heavy leading the charge and two Falcon 9 launches coming...

title: KMI advertises prices for debris removal
summary: Kall Morris Inc. handed out a deck of cards at the Space Symposium to advertise prices the company plans to charge for grabbing space junk.

title: NASA, Rocket Lab Set Coverage for Tropical Cyclones Mission
summary: NASA and Rocket Lab are targeting 9 p.m. EDT, Sunday, April 30 (1 p.m. New Zealand Standard Time, Monday, May 1), to launch two storm tracking CubeSats into orbit.

title: Using Hubble, researchers accidentally discover ejected black hole forcing star creation
summary: Throughout the universe, supermassive black holes can typically be found at the center of massive galaxies that stretch tens of light years across. However, using Hubble, a team of researchers has discovered a supermassive black hole that appears to have been ejected from its galaxy. The black hole, which is around 20 million times more massive than our Sun, is traveling incredibly fast — so fast that it could travel the distance between Earth and the Moon in just 14 minutes.

title: VP Harris, South Korea President Yoon Suk Yeol to Visit NASA Goddard
summary: Vice President Kamala Harris and Republic of Korea (ROK) President Yoon Suk Yeol will visit NASA’s Goddard Space Flight Center in Greenbelt, Maryland, on Tuesday, April 25, to see firsthand the agency’s climate change work. NASA Deputy Administrator Pam Melroy and Goddard Center Director Makenzie Lystrup will join them on tour.
